Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: allowing you to do anything you want while enjoying a full length book.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: My favorite genre to listen to audiobooks is fantasy and historical because I can paint the picture in my mind with little effort.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If someone was to compare an audiobook to reading a book I would say the audiobook is better.
